rComments: I was really excited about this class but ended up really disliking it. The projects were pretty funny but the lectures were very boring and irrelevant. She was very nice and helpful, she tried her best to work with students to make tests/assignments fair.
This was probably the most helpful class I have had yet to date. I feel like Drum understands and wants us to understand and question even more. Great class!!

I am going to be honest, this professor is the epitome of the awful liberal arts college course. The class is taught with pretentiousness and the subjects are often irrelevant. The "projects" not only offer little to no educational value, but are not thoroughly explained, throwing concise definitions into the wind in the favor of ambiguity.

I managed to learn HTML, but not because of her. I had to teach myself. She didn't go over it in class. The kind of stuff we cover is, at least to me, very pretentious to the point of stupidity. I'm not enjoying this class. If you like interpreting stuff in ways the author probably didn't intend, you'll like it. I found myself lost and annoyed. MEH

Video Games and Visual Culture.  There were no sections in this class, but Meredith seemed like a very nice person anyway.  Regardless, she is looking for you to summarize all the important points in the reading responses.  A good TA
